import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['x'], data['y'])
    plt.xlabel('x')
    plt.ylabel('y')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title("What is the correlation between x and y?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))

    plt.xlabel('x')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title("What is the distribution of x?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    distances = np.sqrt(data['x']**2 + data['y']**2)
    plt.hist(distances, bins='auto')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title("What is the distribution of the distance of each point from the origin?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
